Chelicerae (
Fig. 1C
) — Chelicera 150 (147 – 151) in length; Fixed digit with three teeth, pilus dentilis not distinct, movable digit 20 (19 – 21) long and with a tooth (
Fig. 1C
).

Tectum (
Fig. 1D
) — The anterior margin of the tectum convex and pointed antromedially and 25 (23 – 26) wide (
Fig. 1D
).

Spermatheca (
Fig. 1F
) — Calyx dish-like followed by an annulated neck 5 (5 – 6) long and 10 (10 – 11) wide at junction with vesicle; major duct thick and 25 (25 – 26) long, minor duct very fine (
Fig. 1F
).

Remarks — The Iranian new species closely resembles to
Paragigagnathus strunkovae
from Tajikistan in having ventri-anal shield with two pairs of pre anal setae and one pair of pores, only posterior dorsal setae set on prominent tubercles, setae J5 serrated, movable digit of chelicera with one tooth, setae ST4 on metasternal shields, however, it differs from the later by:

2) Spermatheca with dish shaped calyx in new species opposed to funnel shaped in 

P. strunkovae

;

2) Movable digit of chelicera with one tooth in Iranian species whereas two teeth in 

P. bidentatus

;

3) Ventrianal shield with notched anterior margin vs . convex in
P. bidentatus
;

4) Opisthogaster with one slender platelet between setae
JV 4-5
in the former oppose to four platelets in the latter;

2) Dorsal seta 
J5
serrated in the former instead of smooth in latter;

3) Tarsus IV with a macroseta in the new species opposed to absent in 

P. tamaricis

;
